<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB02422</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT RIGHTSIZING THE NATIONAL GOVERNMENT TO IMPROVE PUBLIC SERVICE DELIVERY</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Intends to create a Committee on Rightsizing the National Government, provides for its powers and functions; submission to the President of the rightsized organizational structure of department agencies concerned and submission by the Department Secretaries/Agency Heads to the DBM the detailed organizations structure and staffing pattern.

Proposes retirement benefits and separation incentives for personnel who may be affected by the NG's Rightsizing Program.

Provides for prohibition on appointment or rehiring of personnel retired/separated from the service for a period of five (5) years, except as teaching staff in a state university or college, while consultancy services shall be governed by Sec.7 of R.A. No. 6713 (Code of Conduct and Ethical Standards for Public Officials and Employees).
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>VELASCO, LORD ALLAN JAY Q.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-07-18</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Torres-Gomez (000 2019-09-18)</td><td>2. Savellano (000 2019-10-15)</td><tr><td>3. Vargas (000 2019-11-12)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITEE HEARINGS/ACTIONS:</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp1. Referred to Stakeholders on 2019-09-11</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-Referred to the Department of Budget and Management for position paper.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON GOVERNMENT REORGANIZATION ON 2019-07-29</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SECONDARILY REFERRED TO THE COMMITTEE(S) ON APPROPRIATIONS</td></tr></table>